The bodies of two school rugby players, aged 17 and 18, were recovered at two  Durban beaches on Monday morning ahead of a rugby tournament in which they were meant to play. SAPS spokesperson Lt-Col Nqobile Gwala said “an inquest docket was opened in Point police station for investigation”. Several sources confirmed to TimesLIVE that the Gauteng-based players had  travelled to  KwaZulu-Natal to compete in a  rugby festival which kicked off on Saturday. It is understood that the  pupils had been swimming on Sunday. Police divers from Durban police search and rescue (SAR) and Metro police SAR  recovered the bodies  at Laguna Beach and Country Club beach. This is a developing story. TimesLIVE Support independent journalism by subscribing to the Sunday Times. Just R20 for the first month.